This paper focuses on developing explainable retrieval models for product search, which involves both information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The proposed model also involves embedding and ranking, which are common topics in machine learning (ML) and natural language processing (NLP), leading to cs.LG and cs.CL as likely sub-categories. Finally, the use of a knowledge graph suggests a potential connection to database (DB) research, making it a possible sub-category as well.
